

 A Page Object Model is a test design pattern
 A Page Factory is one way of implementing Page Object Model which is inbuilt in selenium.

In plain POM, you define locators using ‘By’
while in Page Factory, you use @FindBy annotation to define page objects.

Page Object Model is a design approach
while PageFactory is a class which provides implementation of Page Object Model design approach.

In the plain page object model, you need to
initialize every page object individually otherwise you will
encounter NullPointerException

while In PageFactory all page objects are initialized (Lazily) by using initElements() method.
